### 🎮 1. GET ALL GAMES (Should be empty at first)
GET http://localhost:8080/videogames

### 🎮 2. CREATE A GAME (Success)
POST http://localhost:8080videogames
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Elden Ring",
  "price": 59.99
}

### 🎮 3. CREATE DUPLICATE GAME (Should fail with 400 Bad Request!)
# This proves to your professor you handle edge cases!
POST http://localhost:8080/videogames
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Elden Ring",
  "price": 39.99
}


### 👤 4. GET ALL PERSONS (To copy an ID)
# Run this, look at the response, and copy the "id" of one of your users!
GET http://localhost:8080/persons

### ⭐ 5. CREATE A REVIEW (Success)
POST http://localhost:8080/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 10,
  "comment": "Masterpiece. I died 400 times.",
  "authorId": "c8c7e5f9-b9c4-490a-bd51-2f8cfc042dee",
  "gameId": "e189a211-2fc2-43bc-8a9d-0506f8399ef9"
}

### ⭐ 6. CREATE DUPLICATE REVIEW (Should fail with 400 Bad Request!)
# Run the exact same test again to prove a user can only review a game once!
POST http://localhost:8080/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 1,
  "comment": "I changed my mind, this game is too hard.",
  "authorId": "PASTE-THE-SAME-PERSON-UUID-HERE",
  "gameId": "PASTE-THE-SAME-GAME-UUID-HERE"
}